{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"What would you say is a compelling reason for supporting this option -- other than glTF supports it?","created_at":"2017-07-12T22:36:04.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-314917253","id":314917253,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNDkxNzI1Mw==","updated_at":"2017-07-12T22:36:04.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/314917253","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Here's a quote from\r\n```\r\nTightening the Precision of Perspective Rendering\r\nPaul Upchurch, Mathieu Desbrun\r\nJournal of Graphics Tools, Volume 16, Issue 1, 2012\r\n```\r\n> **Infinite Projection versus Standard Projection**<br>\r\n> The difference between the two methods above is 2\u01eb relative error in depth, or 2\u01eb absolute error in depth comparison. Since depth is in the range of [\u22121, 1] a relative (or absolute) error of 2\u01eb is equivalent to a relative error of at least 2\u01eb in depth. <br>\r\n> While the infinite projection method has 2\u01eb better precision and covers view space from the near plane to infinity, one might argue that, if there is no interest in rendering objects beyond a far clipping plane, the smaller depth buckets of a standard projection may be better. It is, however, easy to see that the precision of an infinite projection is better over a larger viewing range than the precision of a finite projection with reasonably large values of `f \/ n`.","created_at":"2017-07-13T12:36:32.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-315064834","id":315064834,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNTA2NDgzNA==","updated_at":"2017-07-13T12:36:32.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/315064834","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3479527?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/lexaknyazev","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0Nzk1Mjc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"lexaknyazev","type":"User","id":3479527,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Yes, I was aware of that paper. \r\n\r\n>Infinite projections are used cautiously since they are assumed to negatively impact precision. This is due to the same number of depth storage bits being distributed across a larger Z range.\r\n\r\n>However, our analysis will show, counterintuitively, that the infinite projection is a more precise general purpose projection and the finite projection is only useful when the depth range ratio is very small or extremely high precision is needed at the near plane.\r\n\r\nThey provide a theoretical result that with an \"infinite\" projection matrix, precision can be improved by 2 machine units _as compared to a finite projection with reasonably large values of f \/ n._\r\n\r\nBut we do not advise users to do that. We advise users to set the near plane to be as large as is reasonable, and to set the far plane reasonably close.\r\n\r\n>What would you say is a compelling reason for supporting this option -- other than glTF supports it?\r\n\r\nI am still interested in hearing of a compelling three.js use case, however. Why is glTF supporting it?\r\n","created_at":"2017-07-13T16:32:02.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-315131779","id":315131779,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNTEzMTc3OQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-13T16:32:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/315131779","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"> Why is glTF supporting it?\r\n\r\nIt was added by request from Oculus. The late Johannes van Waveren was advocating for making infinite projection matrix \"everyone's first choice\".\r\n\r\nFrom recent experiences, models with unusually big dimensions don't show up in [three.js glTF viewer](https:\/\/gltf-viewer.donmccurdy.com\/). Zooming camera out reveals that far plane isn't far enough. E.g.:\r\n![image](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/3479527\/28177952-c245f6b6-680d-11e7-9d64-c354356fae07.png)\r\n\r\nOf course, one could argue that camera planes should be adjusted individually for each model\/scene.","created_at":"2017-07-13T17:03:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-315140353","id":315140353,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNTE0MDM1Mw==","updated_at":"2017-07-13T17:03:17.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/315140353","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3479527?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/lexaknyazev","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0Nzk1Mjc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"lexaknyazev","type":"User","id":3479527,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/lexaknyazev\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">Of course, one could argue that camera planes should be adjusted individually for each model\/scene.\r\n\r\nYeah, that seems like a user-error. Ensure the far plane value is big enough to contain the scene, and set `controls.maxDistance` to a reasonable value.","created_at":"2017-07-13T17:22:33.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-315145259","id":315145259,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNTE0NTI1OQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-13T17:22:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/315145259","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Thanks all, I will improve the drag-and-drop viewer to infer appropriate near\/far planes automatically (https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy\/three-gltf-viewer\/issues\/19).\r\n\r\nWhether three.js should support infinite projection matrices, I will leave to you all.","created_at":"2017-07-13T19:25:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-315177645","id":315177645,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNTE3NzY0NQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-13T19:25:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/315177645","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1848368?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/donmccurdy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDgzNjg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"donmccurdy","type":"User","id":1848368,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/donmccurdy\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Closing, but we can revisit if there is a compelling use case.","created_at":"2017-07-19T03:42:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-316263955","id":316263955,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMxNjI2Mzk1NQ==","updated_at":"2017-07-19T03:42:42.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/316263955","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> making infinite projection matrix \"everyone's first choice\".\r\n\r\nGreat \ud83d\udc4d, because that's obviously the path to least friction for people wanting to just make a scene without fiddling with numbers and having to do math (as easy as CSS `perspective` property); it makes things easier for people.","created_at":"2017-09-26T23:10:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-332361946","id":332361946,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzMjM2MTk0Ng==","updated_at":"2017-09-26T23:10:17.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/332361946","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> Closing, but we can revisit if there is a compelling use case.\r\n\r\n@WestLangley A bunch of people want to do this:\r\n\r\n- Ideally people who know basic web technology (like using CSS 3D `perspective`) would be able to take existing knowledge and apply it in Three.js without friction. (consistency across web technologies and libraries is ideal)\r\n- Some people like to mix CSS3D with WebGL, and not having infinite perspective is a barrier to doing this. Here's a bunch of examples and questions:\r\n  - http:\/\/www.emagix.net\/academic\/mscs-project\/item\/camera-sync-with-css3-and-webgl-threejs\r\n  - http:\/\/learningthreejs.com\/blog\/2013\/04\/30\/closing-the-gap-between-html-and-webgl\/\r\n  - https:\/\/github.com\/jeromeetienne\/threex.htmlmixer (nice demo!)\r\n  - http:\/\/michael-staub.rhcloud.com\/2015\/05\/11\/webvr-mixing-html-and-webgl\/\r\n  - https:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/33768227\r\n  - https:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/24681170\r\n  - http:\/\/adndevblog.typepad.com\/cloud_and_mobile\/2015\/07\/embedding-webpages-in-a-3d-threejs-scene.html\r\n  - http:\/\/www.html5gamedevs.com\/topic\/11910-embedded-html\/\r\n  - https:\/\/docs.argonjs.io\/tutorial\/part2\r\n\r\nSeems like having infinite perspective would be useful if it doesn't exist yet. If CSS 3D can do it, so can Three!","created_at":"2017-09-27T00:57:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755#issuecomment-332377598","id":332377598,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11755","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzMjM3NzU5OA==","updated_at":"2017-09-27T00:58:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/332377598","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/297678?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/trusktr","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5NzY3OA==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"trusktr","type":"User","id":297678,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/trusktr\/orgs"}}]}